    "Description": "Drive Unreal Engine 5.7 from Claude (or any MCP client) over a localhost TCP socket. Twenty-eight tools for editor automation: arbitrary Python execution, Blueprint/Widget tree introspection and mutation, viewport screenshots, actor queries, texture import and configuration, Output Log access, console command execution, asset-registry tag queries, full asset-lifecycle authoring (inspect/move/rename/delete), and Level Sequence introspection + scaffolding (inspect/create/bind-actor). Bypasses UE Python reflection limits by calling native C++ APIs directly.",
